cs.LO, cs.PL, cs.SE, cs.FL, cs.CR 

The paper proposes a deductive proof method for program equivalence using logically constrained term rewriting systems (LCTRSs). This method is based on encoding the language semantics and the two programs as terms. Therefore, the paper is likely to belong to the Logic in Computer Science (cs.LO) sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the formalization of read-sets and write-sets of symbolic expressions and statements, which suggests that it could also belong to the Programming Languages (cs.PL) and Software Engineering (cs.SE) sub-categories. The paper also mentions the verification of program schemas and compiler optimizations, which could place it in the Formal Languages and Automata Theory (cs.FL) and Cryptography and Security (cs.CR) sub-categories.
